      "id": 951,
      "from_id": "cec50b17:0",
      "to_id": "cec50b17:26",
      "content": "Improve the `needs_approval` message UI to handle multi-option questions — add a text input next to the approve button so the human can type a specific reply (like \"option 1\") instead of just clicking the generic approve.\n\n**Work inside:** `.synapse/worktrees/developer-25-needs-approval-ux`\nCommit your changes to that branch. Do not push.\n\n---\n\n**Current behavior:**\nMessages with `needs_approval: true` show a `✓ approve` button. Clicking it calls `POST /api/messages/:id/approve` which sets `approved_at` in DB. There's no way to send a typed reply from that button area.\n\n**What to add:**\nWhen `needs_approval` is true and the message hasn't been approved yet, show a small inline reply input next to the approve button:\n\n```html\n<div class=\"message-actions\">\n  <input class=\"approval-reply-input\" type=\"text\" placeholder=\"reply (optional)\" />\n  <button class=\"msg-approve-btn\" data-msg-id=\"${m.id}\">✓ approve</button>\n</div>\n```\n\nWhen the approve button is clicked:\n1. Read the input value (if any)\n2. Call `POST /api/messages/:id/approve` (existing — marks approved_at)\n3. If the input has text, ALSO post a reply message to the agent: `POST /api/messages` with `{ to_id: m.from_id, content: inputValue, priority: m.priority }`\n\nThis way: clicking approve with no text = simple \"approved\" (same as before), clicking with text = sends the reply AND marks approved.\n\n**`public/app.js`** changes:\n- Update the `approveBtn` template to include the input\n- Update the delegated click handler on `#messages-list` to read the sibling input and post the reply if non-empty\n\n**`public/style.css`** — style the inline input:\n```css\n.approval-reply-input {\n  font-size: 10px;\n  padding: 2px 6px;\n  border-radius: 3px;\n  border: 1px solid var(--border);\n  background: var(--bg);\n  color: var(--text);\n  width: 120px;\n  font-family: inherit;\n}\n```\n\n**Build:** `npm run build` must pass. Commit. Report DONE to cec50b17:0.",
